API Testing 
-----------------
GET  - To get the record details 
POST - To Post the information or create record
DELETE - delete record
PUT(UPDATE) - update record
PATCH (Partial Update)- Partially update the record


End point url 
Path Parameter 
----------------
- we used when we want to identify or fetch specific resource or record

 we append in url
 we use this when value is mandetory 
 Example : https://api.example.com/users/101
 here path parameter is 101


 Query Prameter 
 ---------------
 query parameter is used to filter, sort or modify the result 

 it apears after ? in url 

 Example : https://api.example.com/users?age=25

 here in above example age=25 is a Query Parameter

 Multiple Query Parameters:
 ----------------------------
 Example : https://api.example.com/users?age=25&city=Bangalore


Difference between PUT(Update) and PATCH(Partail Update)
----------------------------------------------------------
PUT (Full Update) - Replace or updte the entire resource or record and if any fields are missed 
               that will update as null or default 

PUT /users/101
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ajith",
  "email": "ajith@example.com",
  "age": 30
}


PATCH(Partail Update) - replace or update only specified fields rest remain as it is 

PATCH /users/101
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "age": 31
}

